The Victims Support Fund (VSF) Task Force on Covid-19, has donated food, non food items, medical, PPE and hygiene product to IDPs and the vulnerable in Adamawa state. Mrs Toyosi Akelere-Ogunsiji, Head of the VSF Task force on Covid-19, while presenting the items at NEMA office in Yola Thursday said, the items are targeted at 10,000 households . Ogunsiji said the only way to encourage people to stay at home during lockdown, is to provide them with scour especially those that do not have access to finance and sustainable economic opportunity to eat. She urged people to embrace personal hygiene practice saying,  community transition of coronavirus is the greatest danger of the pandemic  in the society. “VSF Is committed to avert COVID-19, by providing people with what to eat. “This intervention is the most robust among all the interventions in the country. “Today VSF is giving out 10 kgs of rice, beans maize, 4-liters of vegetable oil, 2-kgs of salt, dettol soap, masks among other per household. “Hand wash is singular measure against contracting coronavirus people to concentrate on it”. According to her medical equipment and drugs is been donated through  the state PHCDA and urged  government to set up wash centers in all the IDPs camps in the state Receiving the items on behalf of the state government, Dr Muhammad Suleiman, Executive  Secretary,  State Emergency Management Agency (ADSEMA),.lauded VSF for the gesture which he described as timely. Sulaiman assured state government’s commitment to ensure judicious utilisation of the items for the targeted beneficiaries. He said the items would be distributed to the three IDP camps in the state. 